---
description: Mandatory gate — physically read agent.md and .claude/copilot-instructions.md before the first response
alwaysApply: true
---

**Execute only if this is the first user message in the conversation — i.e., there are no prior assistant responses visible in context. Skip silently on all subsequent messages.**

Use your file-read tool to open and read both files below in order. Do not paraphrase, infer, or skip. Each file must be a real tool call that returns file content.

1. Open and read [`agent.md`](../../agent.md)
2. Open and read [`.claude/copilot-instructions.md`](../../.claude/copilot-instructions.md)

Once both files have been read and their content is present in context, emit exactly:

> Yes chef!

Then branch based on whether the first message is actionable:

- If the first message contains a command or task (examples: `/commit-github`, "fix this bug", "explain this error", "plan this feature"), continue and handle that request in the same turn after confirming `Yes chef!`.
- If the first message is non-actionable small talk only (examples: "hi", "hello"), stop after `Yes chef!` and wait for the next message.

Do not require the user to resend a first-message command/task.
